<section id="section-1">
  <h2>1. The honest picture: what making money online actually requires</h2>

  <p>Before choosing a method, it helps to understand the three variables that determine how fast you earn and how much. Every legitimate online income path involves some combination of these:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Your time.</strong> How many hours per week can you dedicate consistently? Not "how many hours can I squeeze in this week" — how many, reliably, for the next three to six months.</li>
    <li><strong>Your starting budget.</strong> Some methods require nothing. Others benefit significantly from a small paid traffic budget or a modest tool investment. Knowing your number up front prevents wasted detours.</li>
    <li><strong>Your existing skills.</strong> You do not need technical skills to start most beginner methods, but existing strengths — writing, teaching, a professional background, a specific hobby — create an advantage in specific paths.</li>
  </ul>

